    assessment: "Specimen: fluoride/oxalate (gray top) inhibits glycolysis—without it, glucose decreases 5-7% per hour at room temperature. Alternatively, separate plasma from cells within 30 minutes. Plasma glucose is 10-15% HIGHER than whole blood glucose (plasma has more water content). POC glucose meters: affected by hematocrit (high Hct = falsely low glucose; low Hct = falsely high glucose), altitude, temperature, and certain drugs (maltose, galactose with GDH-PQQ strips).",
