    examPitfalls: ["Guaiac detects ANY heme (human, animal, plant peroxidases); FIT detects only HUMAN hemoglobin—critical distinction", "Rehydration of guaiac slides (adding water before developer) increases sensitivity but DECREASES specificity (more false positives)", "FIT is less sensitive for UPPER GI bleeding—upper GI hemoglobin is digested and no longer immunoreactive"],
